# 🎨 Google Stitch — Complete Feature Guide

**Google Stitch** is an AI-powered UI design platform (currently in BETA) that turns text prompts, screenshots, or URLs into beautiful, functional website and app designs — with exportable code.

You already have **Stitch connected** through this AI assistant via the **StitchMCP** integration. This means you can design websites directly from this chat!

---

## ✅ Stitch Skills Available RIGHT NOW (via this AI)

These are the Stitch "skills" you can use directly in this conversation:

| Skill | What it Does | How to Ask |
|---|---|---|
| **Generate Screen** | Create a new UI screen from a text description | *"Create a landing page for a fitness app"* |
| **Edit Screens** | Modify existing screens with instructions | *"Make the buttons more rounded and change color to blue"* |
| **Create Design System** | Set up colors, fonts, shapes, branding | *"Create a dark mode design system with purple accents"* |
| **Update Design System** | Change the overall visual theme | *"Switch to a light mode with green primary color"* |
| **Apply Design System** | Apply a theme to your screens | *"Apply my design system to all screens"* |
| **Generate Variants** | Create multiple design variations | *"Generate 3 variants of this homepage"* |
| **List/Create Projects** | Manage your Stitch projects | *"Create a new project called 'My Portfolio'"* |
| **List Screens** | See all screens in a project | *"Show me all screens in my project"* |

